    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Five mesh densities were evaluated, ranging from a coarse 42,000-element discretization to a fine 310,000-element discretization. Construct stiffness and yield force QoIs were monitored across refinement levels. The study confirmed that the medium-density mesh (approximately 185,000 elements) achieved QoI convergence within 0.8%, satisfying the discretization error acceptance criterion. Results informed the production mesh selection used in all subsequent validation simulations.",
